Description . Male . Measurements: BL 6.25, CL 3.40, CW 2.50, PLE 0.35, PME 0.20 (AMS KS31749). Female . Measurements: BL 6.25, CL 3.20, CW 2.40, PLE 0.35, PME 0.20 (AMS KS68199). For morphological description see species diagnosis and generic description.
Etymology . The specific name is in honour of Dr M.R. Gray for his contributions to Australian arachnology.
Distribution . Known from south eastern New South Wales ( Fig. 27b ).

caption.paragraph:
Fig. 17.
Storenosoma grayi . (a–b)
male palp (KS31749): (a) ventral; (b) RTA, retrolateral. (c–d) female genitalia (KS69899): (c) epigynum, ventral; (d) internal. Scale lines 0.25 mm.

subSubSection.paragraph: Remarks . This species is known from the type locality, near Gerringong, south to the forests west of Moruya. Males from the southern end of the range have a less prominent TA and the proximal projection of the MA is narrower and more curved.
